使用说明&gt;&gt;&gt; import hashpumpy&gt;&gt;&gt; help(hashpumpy.hashpump)Help on built-in function hashpump in module hashpumpy:hashpump(...) hashpump(hexdigest, original_data, data_to_add, key_length) -&gt; (digest, message) Arguments: hexdigest(str): Hex-encoded result of hashing key + original_data. original_data(str): Known data used to get the hash result hexdigest. data_to_add(str): Data to append key_length(int): Length of unknown data prepended to the hash Returns: A tuple containing the new hex digest and the new message.&gt;&gt;&gt; hashpumpy.hashpump(&#x27;ffffffff&#x27;, &#x27;original_data&#x27;, &#x27;data_to_add&#x27;, len(&#x27;KEYKEYKEY&#x27;))(&#x27;e3c4a05f&#x27;, &#x27;original_datadata_to_add&#x27;)

